This paper discusses coordination languages and technologies, which are commonly used in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses programming technologies and their evaluation criteria, which falls under the scope of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses black-box componentization and interface extensibility, which are related to programming languages and their design, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions run-time optimization goals, which can be related to cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
